      "repair_reason": "Human review is required because this member PR has protected maintainer and clawsweeper:human-review handling after an explicit stop, and the remaining blockers are security-sensitive proxy policy defects.; Needs attention: The diff still leaves direct loopback paths where the new managed-proxy policy says traffic should be proxied or limited to the configured Gateway URL.; Review finding: [P1] Carry the configured... (sha=003f15f2c009cb1814eea4e00d17b0680e8addf5)",
      "review_summary": "The PR adds `proxy.loopbackMode`, GatewayClient loopback proxy policy handling, proxy docs/schema/changelog updates, and targeted Gateway/TUI/ACP/node-host coverage.\n\nReproducibility: yes. by source inspection. A bypassed local control-plane CLI can inherit `OPENCLAW_PROXY_ACTIVE=1` and `OPENCLAW_PROXY_LOOPBACK_MODE=proxy` without bootstrapping the proxy stack, and the configured-target bypass gap is visible because the computed configured connection is not passed into `GatewayClient`.",
